                        </p>
                        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-3 mb-6">
                            <li><strong>Seamanship & Rigging:</strong> Knowing different types of ropes (synthetic, wire, natural fiber), how to maintain them, and how to tie essential knots, bends, and splices.</li>
                            <li><strong>Vessel Nomenclature & Construction:</strong> Identifying basic components of a merchant ship, including the bow, stern, forecastle, bilge, draft marks, and Plimsoll line.</li>
                            <li><strong>Anchor and Mooring Work:</strong> Safe handling of the windlass, anchor parts, mooring winches, fairleads, bitts, and lines during berthing operations.</li>
